<subSubSection id="E7F6CAEC4306363DFF41E6C5FCCADAB2" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="6" pageNumber="141" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AF53996743063631FF41E6C5FE2BDCD4" blockId="6.[136,1451,1920,2090]" pageId="6" pageNumber="141">
Etymology:—Latin, ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="68ECE2E443063631FEB6E6C5FDA5DCF0" authorityName="N. K. Zeng, Yi Wang, Xu Zhang &amp; Zhui Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[383,549,1920,1946]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" genus="Tylopilus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="6" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="yangzhuliangii">
<emphasis id="9D98457543063631FEB6E6C5FDA5DCF0" box="[383,549,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="141">yangzhuliangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is named after the Chinese mycologist, Zhu L. Yang, in honor of his great contribution to mycology.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF53996743063631FF74E68DFEA7D340" blockId="6.[136,1451,1920,2090]" pageId="6" pageNumber="141">Diagnosis:—Characterized by very small basidiomes, a peacock blue to deep turquoise pileus, the hymenophore bruising reddish brown when injured, and a slightly interwoven trichodermium composed of uninflated hyphae forming the pileipellis.</paragraph>
<caption id="FB93C9EF43073630FF41E684FDD4DC91" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450771" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6450771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450771/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="142" startId="7.[136,229,1985,2007]" targetBox="[153,1434,190,1958]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="AF53996743073630FF41E684FDD4DC91" blockId="7.[136,1451,1985,2043]" pageId="7" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="9D98457543073630FF41E684FF7FDCBC" bold="true" box="[136,255,1985,2007]" pageId="7" pageNumber="142">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Phylogram inferred from a combined (28S, ITS and 
<emphasis id="9D98457543073630FCC1E687FCBFDCBD" box="[776,831,1986,2007]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="142">TEF1</emphasis>
) dataset using RAxML. BS ≥ 50% and PP ≥ 0.95 are indicated above or below the branches as RAxML BS/PP.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="FB93C9EF4308363FFF41E71FFAF4DD1A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450773" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6450773" box="[136,1396,1626,1649]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450773/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="143" startId="8.[136,229,1626,1648]" targetBox="[151,1436,190,1602]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="AF5399674308363FFF41E71FFAF4DD1A" blockId="8.[136,1396,1626,1649]" box="[136,1396,1626,1649]" pageId="8" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="9D9845754308363FFF41E71FFF7EDD05" bold="true" box="[136,254,1626,1648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="143">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Basidiomes of 
<taxonomicName id="68ECE2E44308363FFE5AE71EFD00DD1A" authorityName="N. K. Zeng, Yi Wang, Xu Zhang &amp; Zhui Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[403,640,1627,1648]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" genus="Tylopilus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="8" pageNumber="143" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="yangzhuliangii">
<emphasis id="9D9845754308363FFE5AE71EFD00DD1A" box="[403,640,1627,1648]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="143">Tylopilus yangzhuliangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (a from FHMU2930, holotype; b–c from FHMU2921). Photos by N.K. Zeng.
</paragraph>
